Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_lib_arcs(25.10)                                  report_lib_arcs(25.10)

Name
       report_lib_arcs

Syntax
       report_lib_arcs

        [-help]

        -arc <string>

        [-fall]

       [-nldm]

        [-quiet]

        [-rise]

       [-lvf  [-early]]

       [-lvf  [-late]]

       [-moments  [-mean_shift]]

        [-moments  [-std_dev]]

       [-moments  [-skewness]]

       [-input_net_transition <float> | -constrained_pin_transition <float>]

        [-input_net_transition <float> | -related_pin_transition <float>]

       [-total_output_net_capacitance  <float>  |  -constrained_pin_transition
       <float>]

        [-total_output_net_capacitance   <float>   |   -related_pin_transition
       <float>]

        [-constrained_pin_transition     <float>    |    -delay    ]    [-con-
       strained_pin_transition <float> | -transition ]

       [-related_pin_transition <float> | -delay ]

        [-related_pin_transition <float> | -transition ]

       Reports the library arc data. The command also returns the  data  in  a
       Tcl object, which can be used in scripts.

       This  command  uses a collection of arcs as input, which can be queried
       using the get_lib_arcs command.

       The units for the input and output  data  can  be  obtained  using  the
       get_time_unit and get_capacitance_unit commands.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -arc <string>
              Specifies the arc(s) for which the report is to be printed.

       -constrained_pin_transition <float>
              Specifies  the  constrained pin slew (valid for constraint arcs)
              at which the parameters need to be reported.

              The slew units must be specified using  the  get_time_unit  com-
              mand.

       -delay Specifies if delay is to be reported.

       -early Specifies if early LVF data is to be reported.

              This parameter can be used only in conjunction with the -lvf.

       -fall  Specifies if details of fall tables are to be reported.

       -input_net_transition <float>
              Specifies the slew at which the parameters need to be reported.

              The  slew  units  must be specified using the get_time_unit com-
              mand.

       -late  Specifies if late LVF data is to be reported.

              This parameter can be used only in conjunction with the -lvf.

       -lvf   Specifies if LVF data is to be reported.

       -mean_shift
              Specifies if the mean shift data is to be reported.

              This parameter can be used only in  conjunction  with  the  -mo-
              ments.

       -moments
              Specifies if moments data is to be reported.

       -nldm  Specifies if NLDM data is to be reported.

       -quiet Disables output to be displayed on the screen.

       -related_pin_transition <float>
              Specifies  the  related  pin slew (valid for constraint arcs) at
              which the parameters need to be reported.

              The slew units must be specified using  the  get_time_unit  com-
              mand.

       -rise  Specifies if details of rise tables are to be reported.

       -skewness
              Specifies if skewness data is to be reported.

              This  parameter  can  be  used only in conjunction with the -mo-
              ments.

       -std_dev
              Specifies if standard deviation data is to be reported.

              This parameter can be used only in  conjunction  with  the  -mo-
              ments.

       -total_output_net_capacitance <float>
              Specifies the load at which the parameters need to be reported.

              The  load  must be specified using the get_capacitance_unit com-
              mand.

       -transition
              Specifies if the output slew is to be reported.

Examples
              * The following command reports the library arc data  containing
                mean shift rise tables:

                report_lib_arcs  -arc  [get_lib_arcs  -from  cell_w/DFF/CK -to
                cell_w/DFF/Q] -input_net_transition 0.08 /

                       -total_output_net_capacitance 0.055  -mean_shift  -rise
                -delay -moments -nldm

                Units of Report:- Time: '1000ps', Capacitance: '1000fF'.

                input_net_transition:0.080000,        total_output_net_capaci-
                tance:0.055000

                --------------------------------------------------------------------

                | Index | Timing Arc | Value(s) |

                |
                ------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

                |       | Cell       | Source/Sink Pin | Timing Sense | Timing
                Type | cell_rise |

                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                | 1     | cell_w/DFF | CK -> Q         | non_unate     |  ris-
                ing_edge | 0.258444  |

                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                {{cell_rise 0.258444279432} {ocv_mean_shift_cell_rise NA}}

              * The  following command reports the library arc data containing
                fall tables for moments data:

                report_lib_arcs  -arc  [get_lib_arcs  -from  cell_w/BUF/A  -to
                cell_w/BUF/Y] /

                    -input_net_transition  0.055 -total_output_net_capacitance
                0.15 -fall -delay -moments -nldm

                Units of Report:- Time: '1000ps', Capacitance: '1000fF'.

                input_net_transition:0.055000,        total_output_net_capaci-
                tance:0.150000

                -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                |            Index            |           Timing           Arc
                | Value(s)   |

                |
                ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

                |       | Cell       | Source/Sink Pin | Timing Sense   | Tim-
                ing Type  | cell_fall  |

                -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                | 1     | cell_w/BUF | A -> Y          | positive_unate | com-
                binational| 0.129744   |

                --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                {{cell_fall      0.129}       {ocv_std_dev_cell_fall       NA}
                {ocv_mean_shift_cell_fall NA} {ocv_skewness_cell_fall NA}}

              * The  following command reports the library arc data containing
                rise tables data with output slew:

                report_lib_arcs -arc  [get_lib_arcs  -from  cell_w/DFF/CK  -to
                cell_w/DFF/Q] -input_net_transition 0.08 /

                     -total_output_net_capacitance   0.055  -mean_shift  -rise
                -delay -moments -nldm -transition

                Units of Report:- Time: '1000ps', Capacitance: '1000fF'.

                input_net_transition:0.080000,        total_output_net_capaci-
                tance:0.055000

                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                |            Index            |           Timing           Arc
                | Value(s)  |

                |
                -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                |       | Cell       | Source/Sink Pin | Timing Sense | Timing
                Type | rise_transition | cell_rise |

                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                | 1     | cell_w/DFF | CK -> Q         | non_unate     |  ris-
                ing_edge | 0.21692         | 0.258444  |

                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                {{cell_rise        0.258}        {rise_transition       0.216}
                {ocv_mean_shift_cell_rise NA}  {ocv_mean_shift_rise_transition
                NA}}

                This command also returns the data in a Tcl object that can be
                parsed  and used in scripts. A 3-Dimensional Tcl List will re-
                turn the following information:

                {{TableName  Value}  {TableName  Value}}  {{TableName   Value}
                {TableName Value}}

                Here,  the  first list (left column) indicates the Table-Value
                pair in one arc. The second list indicates the various  tables
                present  per  arc.  And the third list (last column) indicates
                the list of total arcs in the collection.

              * The following command reports the slew and capacitance load:

                set  items  [report_lib_arcs   -arc   [   get_lib_arcs   -from
                sc_cmoslp/AO22X/clk -to sc_cmoslp/AO22X /out1] /

                     -input_net_transition 0.003 -total_output_net_capacitance
                0.021]

                Units of Report:- Time: '1000ps', Capacitance: '1000fF'.

                input_net_transition:0.003, total_output_net_capacitance:0.021

                ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                |            Index            |           Timing           Arc
                | Value(s) |

                |-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                |       | Cell            | Source/Sink Pin | Timing Sense   |
                Timing Type   | rise_transition | fall_transition |  cell_rise
                | cell_fall |

                ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                | 1     | sc_cmoslp/AO22X | clk -> out1     | positive_unate |
                combinational  |  0.20**           |  0.30**          | 1.00**
                | 1.20**    |

                ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                | 2     | sc_cmoslp/AO22X | clk -> out1     | negative_unate |
                combinational | 0.20**           |  0.30**           |  1.00**
                | 1.20**    |

                ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                **  --> Scalar Value{{cell_rise 0.999} {rise_transition 0.199}
                {cell_fall 1.199} {fall_transition 0.299}} {{cell_rise  0.999}
                {rise_transition  0.199}  {cell_fall  1.199}  {fall_transition
                0.299}}

                tempus 5 > puts $items

                {{cell_rise 0.999} {rise_transition 0.199}  {cell_fall  1.199}
                {fall_transition  0.299}}  {{cell_rise 0.999} {rise_transition
                0.199} {cell_fall 1.199} {fall_transition 0.299}}

